==English==

===Etymology===
From scientific {{etyl|la}} ''[[Onchocerca]]'' (a genus of parasitic worms, from {{etyl|grc}} {{term|lang=grc|ὄγκος}} ‘barb’ + {{term|lang=grc|κέρκος}} ‘tail’) + ''[[-iasis]]''.

===Pronunciation===
* {{IPA|/ɒŋkəsɜːˈkaɪəsɪs/}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun|onchocerciases|-}}

# {{medicine}} A disease caused by a [[worm]] of the genus ''Onchocerca'', especially as transmitted to humans by flies and often causing [[blindness]]; common in tropical Africa.

